# Plan: Add Pagination to GET /users Endpoint

## Context

The `GET /users` endpoint in `src/routes.ts` (line 7-9) currently returns the entire `users` array (15 items) as a flat JSON response. The test suite (`tests/routes.test.ts`) already expects paginated behavior with `page`/`limit` query parameters and a `{ data, pagination }` response shape. All 4 pagination tests currently fail.

## File to Modify

**`src/routes.ts`** — this is the only file that needs changes.

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Update the GET /users handler (lines 6–9)

Replace the current handler:

```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  res.json(users);
});
```

With a paginated version:

```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page as string, 10) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10);
  const total = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data = users.slice(start, start + limit);

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

**Logic breakdown:**
- `page` defaults to `1`, `limit` defaults to `10`, both floored at `1` via `Math.max`
- `totalPages` = `ceil(15 / limit)` (e.g., `ceil(15/10) = 2`, `ceil(15/5) = 3`)
- `start` index computed from page; `Array.slice` naturally returns `[]` when `start` exceeds array length (handles out-of-range pages gracefully — no error needed)
- Response shape: `{ data: User[], pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } }`

No other files (types, data, app, tests) require changes.

## Verification

Run the existing test suite:

```bash
npx vitest run
```

All 6 tests should pass (4 pagination + 2 single-user):

| Test | Key assertion |
|------|--------------|
| default page & limit | `data.length === 10`, `pagination === {page:1, limit:10, total:15, totalPages:2}` |
| second page | `data.length === 5`, `page === 2` |
| custom limit=5 | `data.length === 5`, `totalPages === 3` |
| out-of-range page=100 | `data === []`, `page === 100` |
| GET /users/1 | `name === "Alice Johnson"` |
| GET /users/999 | `status === 404` |

